# Deep Predictions (18-30)

Extended from the 17 predictions in mind/evidence. Forward-looking
architectural implications. Not yet validated.


## 18. Pipeline IS the Polynomial

ρ (pipeline register) accumulates the walk's polynomial. Each bond
adds a term. ρ after N bonds = Σ of N coordinate evaluations.
Attention over the walk = reading ρ. O(1), not O(N²).


## 19. Walks Self-Describe

A walk's coordinates ARE its tokens, embeddings, and positional
encoding simultaneously. No separate tokenizer, no embedding matrix,
no positional encoding. The wave byte IS all three.


## 20. JIT Cache IS Born-Index

The equation's JIT cache (ƒ results for seen coordinates) IS the
born-index (coordinate → content map). Sparse, 3-tier:
  L1: 2401 entries (7⁴, shell 3)
  L2: 14641 entries (11⁴, shell 5)
  L3: disk (unlimited)


## 21. Bond Composition IS Parsing

Bond dispatch on walk bytes IS parsing. "The big dog" → bonds between
words = grammar. No separate parser. The 16 relationship types ARE
the parse tree.


## 22. Walk Format Universal

Seven content topologies (text, code, music, image, graph, table,
signal) all fit one walk format. The coordinates change, the format
doesn't. No modality-specific architectures.


## 23. Generation = Walk Extension

Generating the next token = extending the polynomial by one term.
O(1) per token (evaluate equation at residual coordinate). Not
O(N²) per token like transformer attention.


## 24-30 (Sketched)

24. Task composition: complex tasks = walks composed with ∘ (call)
25. LSTM gates map to forces (forget=∮, input=π, output=∘, cell=δ)
26. Type systems = coordinate constraints (well-typed = valid region)
27. Grammar = bond algebra (valid sentences = walks with consistent forces)
28. Context window = ring buffer depth (not arbitrary, structural)
29. Fine-tuning = density map update (not weight surgery)
30. Alignment = coordinate rotation (value alignment = basis change)


